history.content:
1) The people you want to ask are the DS team, not the CS/EECS team since the enrolment block is on the DS side of things.

2) By definition since you're on the waitlist it's not guaranteed that you'll end up in the class (although I'll agree with you that it's highly likely), so I don't think the DS team will budge and instead will tell you to get into EECS 16A before enrolling in Data 100, but your best bet is to ask them.

I find myself <10 on the waitlist to EECS16A (declared, junior), so I am assuming that I will get into the course once the reserved seating is removed in the adjustment period. However, I am looking to enroll in Data C100 right now in Phase II, and CalCentral blocks me from enrolling due to not having the co-req of 16a. Is there a way I can waive this co-req for the system, as I will end up being in EECS16A, but am not currently?
history.subject: EE16A + Data 100
